{
  "text": "The voltage between different points of the circuit, as shown in figure 3 , is monitored as a function of time with an educational data acquisition system, CASSY2. [CITATION_1] The current is measured as the voltage across a 118 mm long piece of the line feed between the capacitor and coil. The measurement line is fit into a sawn slit and fixed by cold forging. The line resistance of 0.065 m is determined from the voltage with a 10 A test current. It coincides well with the value 0.063 m calculated from dimensions. In the same manner, the total ohmic resistance without the switch is measured as 2.67 m . The expected value from the copper dimension is 2.60 m , of which the coil contributes 2.37 m . The contact resistance at the connectors' interfaces is therefore almost negligible. The resistance of the switch is nonlinear, and there is a constant voltage drop at the pn-junction. At high current, the internal differential resistance of the switch is 0.18 m .",
